cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.DC

This paper proposes a framework for enhancing the performance of Differential Evolution (DE), which is a type of evolutionary algorithm commonly used in optimization problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of computational resources and individual preferences, which suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of parallel structures, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
